  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Clinical Program Coordinator (West)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with clinician champions to identify surgical patients for inclusion in the Programme</li><li>Collect and review preoperative, operative, and postoperative clinical data using hospital medical record systems</li><li>Conduct patient follow-ups to monitor recovery and responses to treatment and care plans</li><li>Attend weekly Morbidity & Mortality conferences to capture postoperative outcomes and events</li><li>Ensure accurate, complete, and timely data entry into the Programme database in line with caseload requirements</li><li>Use software applications to support data collection, tracking, and basic analysis</li><li>Ensure appropriate use of resources to obtain reliable and valid clinical data</li><li>Identify opportunities to streamline workflows and improve data collection processes</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma qualification</li><li>Nursing, medical, or healthcare-related background preferred</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook)</li><li>Strong attention to detail with the ability to handle accurate data collection and entry</li><li>Comfortable working with data collection tools and basic data analysis</li><li>Basic understanding of surgical patient care and common procedures is an advantage</li><li>Good teamwork, problem-solving, and time management skills</li><li>Able to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines</li></ul><p>Email: Nurul.amirah@gmprecruit.com <br /><br /><strong>** This Singapore-based position is opened to Singaporeans only.</strong></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence: 11C3793   |   Nurul Amirah |   Registration No: R22108940</p>",
